H1> Working with banners

P> The Banners admin lets you run multiple advertising or promotional [b]campaigns[/b] in parallel and place them anywhere in your theme.

SHOT> banners/banner-admin.png | Banner manager listing active campaigns

H1> Common questions

Q> I defined a new banner from the admin area but it's not showing up – why?
A> Your theme has to be told to display a banner. Open the theme's `theme.php` and make sure you have `{BANNER}` or `{BANNER=yourcampaignname}` in the `$HEADER` section.

Q> I want one set of banners in one area and a different set in another area – how?
A> Group your banners under [b]campaigns[/b] and reference each campaign from the theme:

STEP> Create campaign `cam_1` and add its banners.
STEP> Create campaign `cam_2` and add its banners.
STEP> In `theme.php`, place `{BANNER=cam_1}` where you want the first set.
STEP> Place `{BANNER=cam_2}` where you want the second set.
STEP> Use a bare `{BANNER}` to mix banners from every campaign at random.

Q> What's the client login and client password for?
A> You can define a login and password for each banner client. They use them to access reports about how their banners are performing by visiting `http://yoursite.com/banner.php` and entering their credentials.

H1> Tower banners inside a menu item

P> Tower (vertical) banners look out of place in a header bar. The cleanest way to display them is through the dedicated Banner menu.

STEP> Open [b]Admin → Banners[/b] and add your tower banners to a new campaign, e.g. `towers`.
STEP> Open [b]Admin → Menus[/b] and activate [b]Banner_menu[/b] in the column where you want the towers.
STEP> Click [b]Configure[/b] on the menu item.
STEP> Set the caption (default is "Advertisement") and enter the campaign name `towers`.
STEP> Save and visit the front page – the tower banners are now in the chosen column.

